The paper discusses the reconstruction of an object's shape or surface from a set of 3D points, which is a common topic in computer graphics and medical image analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), graphics (cs.GR), multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Among these, cs.CV and cs.GR are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the problem of surface reconstruction from 3D point clouds. The use of a statistical shape model (SSM) and a point distribution model (PDM) also suggests a potential connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence these categories are also likely.
